  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Fracture of the upper extremity of the femur is a condition whose frequency increases with&#xD;
      age. It is a serious disease, with multiple consequences such as a decrease in life&#xD;
      expectancy, quality of life and patient autonomy. In this observational study, the&#xD;
      investigators wish to evaluate the evolution of the autonomy of very elderly patients&#xD;
      operated on for an upper extremity femur fracture as a function of early post-operative&#xD;
      anemia.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
